This package is a set of Python bindings for the Open Database Transfer
Protocol client library. It is compliant with the Python Database API 
Specification v2.0 (see PEP 249 for details).

ODBTP is a TCP/IP protocol for connecting to Win32-based databases from any
platform. See http://http://odbtp.sourceforge.net/ for more information.

To install this package, copy or symlink the odbtp subdirectory into your
python path. At that point, you should be able to use the library by entering:

import odbtp

in a python program. See the aformentioned PEP 249 for details on the API.

